This game was good for a while, but know I just find the game annoying. Partner pokemon constantly need feed even when you sign out of the game. Changes in the Setting are undone after signing out of the game. Gifts are useless on players with no friends. And of course Meltan the only pokemon found in the game can only be caught during a one time event. From these reasons alone, I have no intention on playing this game ever again. I recommend not playing till further notice.

The good: It's fun to collect all the pokemon, It's great to be outdoors and explore, doing raids with friends is enjoyable. The bad: Battles are childishly simplistic with few moves and teams of only 3, CP caps are arbitrary, Atk, def, and spd stats are poorly explained, stardust takes an obscenely long time to collect, even with active bonuses, the game is extremely grindy, & the whale fishing microtransaction store. Overall: Play for the collection aspect. Nothing else is very substantial.

The game is being rigged. Terrible matchmaking. You will face the same stuff every time until you change your team to something else. It will error you out if you match with the opponent you were not supposed to. Error 6 when you turn off your location. Error 1 does not allow you to even play and you instantly lose the game. And i will never forget the time where you could not even do anything but watch your pokemon go down while your charge move and switch button disappear. Most sickening times. The game is so broken. You have to restart the app every few battles to avoid all the bugs and lag. And hiding elo points in the future is throwing an even thicker curtain over the players heads. How does this game design make any sense? It is so disgusting the delays after charge moves calculating every win con for the game to be as rigged as possible.
